 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search This job has expired on Indeed Reasons could include: the employer is not accepting applications, is not actively hiring, or is reviewing applications Product Designer, Assistant Facebook Burlingame, CA 94010 Come be a part of a team of designers, engineers and artists passionate about creating compelling products for Facebook's billions of users. As a Product Designer for the Assistant Design Team, you will be involved in every aspect of the product development process from brainstorming to tweaking pixels and content right before launch.You will be expected to utilize your full range of product design, systems design, interaction design, and visual design skills, and you will own the experience for a wide area of the Assistant product. You will build upon your existing skill-set and passion for multi-modal interaction and systems problem solving, and help define the next generation of multimodal conversational experiences for our Facebook family of apps, as well as our emerging AR and VR products.We are looking for an experienced and talented Product Designer to conceptualize, illustrate, build and deliver innovative conversational systems, tools, and products. You will be expected to drive these experiences from concepts and storyboards to product launch with attention to detail through elegant probabilistic designs that allow humans to interact more naturally with our devices. A positive and collaborative attitude is required, and we’re looking for a self-motivated problem solver with impeccable communication skills. 
Conceptualize and iterate on high-quality end-to-end designs for conversational user interfaces 
Deliver high quality pixels integrating conversational products into surfaces across the Facebook family of apps and emerging AR and VR products 
Contribute to high-level strategic decisions with the rest of the product and executive teams 
Document standards, frameworks, processes and methodology 
Clearly articulate your vision, strategy and design to cross-functional teams and executive stakeholders 
Collaborate with PMs, engineers, art team, researchers, conversation designers and content strategists to oversee the user experience of a product from conception until launch 
Create and prototype pre-visualizations to help communicate UI/UX ideas 
Give and solicit feedback from other designers in order to continually raise our bar for quality 
Be an advocate for the design community within FRL, and across all of Facebook 
Experience shipping at least 1 conversational or AI product 
Portfolio featuring examples of multi-modal conversational experiences 
Experience crafting demos that showcase the potential of conversational experiences 
Proven experience to contribute to design for products in a cross-functional environment 
Knowledge of how qualitative and quantitative research can improve your designs 
Product thinking and design experience in conversational and AI design spaces 
Knowledge and experience with natural language understanding and generation systems 
Experience designing for Assistant, AI, machine learning, or AR/VR products 
Experience creating multiple demos or prototypes showcasing the bleeding edge capabilities of conversational design 
Experience driving and iterating at every phase of design, from paper to pixels 
Facebook's mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we're building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we're creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities - we're just getting started. 
